Quote: After each long and dusty day the James topdressing pilots returned to Rotorua aerodrome and quenched their thirst at the old Geyser Hotel, Whakarewarewa. "Chris" Christoffels, the engineer at Rotorua, painted a typically English pub sign, The Dung Duster's Arms, and this hung in a prominent place behind the bar.
